# Intellectual property boundary

Do **not** add product intellectual property to this public repository.

| Belongs in `driftguard-cloud` only | OK in this OSS repo |
|-----------------------------------|---------------------|
| Product roadmap, CP/LAB/GTM/HANDBOOK task IDs | User-facing quick start, guides, reference |
| Pricing strategy, COGS, packaging specs | OPEN_CORE.md boundary (high level) |
| GTM, founding lab, enterprise playbooks | Gate ladder, MockDrift/CI docs |
| Handbook (mission, ICP, operating metrics) | Hosted API index with link-outs |
| Hosted implementation specs | Technical ADRs for OSS client |
| Design research / UX audits of named products | Generic UX pattern names only |
| Competitive positioning & moat analysis | Factual integration coexistence guides |

**Naming:** Do not use branch names, PR titles, commits, or public docs that say DriftGuard is "modeled after", "inspired by", or "parity with" a specific commercial product. See [IP-BOUNDARY-POLICY.md](../../docs/policies/IP-BOUNDARY-POLICY.md).

When asked to document roadmap, GTM, or pricing — work in **`driftguard-cloud`**. Link to [driftguard.org](https://driftguard.org) for public users.

See [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) § Intellectual property and [OPEN_CORE.md](../../OPEN_CORE.md).
